---
/**
 * An inline Serbian term sitting inside English prose. Carries `lang="sr"`
 * (Serbian uses localized Cyrillic glyph forms, so this is required, not
 * decorative) together with the shared "chip" styling that sets the token apart
 * from the surrounding English text.
 *
 * Use it only for inline terms within running prose. Full-Serbian table cells
 * (a whole declension or conjugation column) don't need it. There the entire
 * cell is already, unambiguously, Serbian.
 */
---

<span lang="sr" class="rounded bg-primary-soft px-1.5 py-0.5 font-medium"><slot /></span>
